<EFX_NOTES_TO_FINANCIAL_STATEMENT>
<A NAME="FIS_NOTES_TO_FINANCIAL_STATEMENT"></A>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	NOTES TO CONSOLIDATED FINANCIAL STATEMENTS
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
	&nbsp;
</P>
</DIV>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	1. B
</FONT>
<A NAME="HCKT-20160101X10K_HTM_NOTES">
</A>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	asis of Presentation and General Information
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:4.5PT 0PT 0PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Nature of Business
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:5PT 0PT;TEXT-INDENT:49.5PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;TEXT-DECORATION:NONE;">
	The Hackett Group
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	is an intellectual property-based strategic consultancy and leading enterprise
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;TEXT-DECORATION:NONE;">
	benchmarking
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	and best practices implementation firm to global companies. Services include business transformation,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;TEXT-DECORATION:NONE;">
	enterprise performance management
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	, &nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;TEXT-DECORATION:NONE;">
	working capital management
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	, and
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;TEXT-DECORATION:NONE;">
	global business services
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	. The Hackett Group also provides dedicated expertise in business strategy, operations, finance, human capital management, strategic sourcing, procurement, and information technology, including its award-winning Oracle EPM and SAP practices.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:13.5PT 0PT 0PT;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Basis of Presentation and Consolidation
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:4.5PT 0PT 0PT;TEXT-INDENT:24.5PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	The accompanying consolidated financial statements include the Company&#x2019;s accounts and those of its wholly-owned subsidiaries which the Company is required to consolidate. The Company consolidates the assets, liabilities, and results of operations of its entities.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:13.5PT 0PT 0PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Fiscal Year
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:4.5PT 0PT 0PT;TEXT-INDENT:24.5PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	The Company&#x2019;s fiscal year generally consists of a 52-week period and periodically consists of a 53-week period as each fiscal year ends on the Friday closest to December&nbsp;31. Fiscal years
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	201
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	5
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	, 201
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	4
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	and 201
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	3
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	ended on
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	January
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	1
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	, 201
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	6
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	, &nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	January 2, 2015
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	and
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	December 2
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	7
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	, 201
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	3
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	, respectively. References to a year included in the consolidated financial statements refer to a fiscal year rather than a calendar year.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:13.5PT 0PT 0PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Cash and Cash Equivalents and Restricted Cash
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:4.5PT 0PT 0PT;TEXT-INDENT:24.5PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	The Company considers all short-term investments with maturities of three months or less to be cash equivalents. Due to the short maturity period of cash equivalents, the carrying amount of these instruments approximates fair market value. The Company places its temporary cash investments with high credit quality financial institutions. At times, such investments may be in excess of the F.D.I.C. insurance limits. The Company has not experienced any loss to date on these investments.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:9PT 0PT 0PT;TEXT-INDENT:24.5PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	As of January 1, 2016 and January 2, 2015
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	, the Company did not have any restricted cash balances.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:13.5PT 0PT 0PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Allowance for Doubtful Accounts
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:4.5PT 0PT 0PT;TEXT-INDENT:27PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	The Company maintains allowances for doubtful accounts for estimated losses resulting from its clients not making required payments. Management makes estimates of the collec
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	tability of accounts receivable
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	and
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	critica
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	lly reviews accounts receivable
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	and analyzes historical bad debts, past-due accounts, client credit-worthiness and current economic trends when evaluating the adequacy of the allowance for doubtful accounts.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	If the financial condition of the Company&#x2019;s clients were to deteriorate, resulting in their inability to make payments, additional allowances may be required.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:13.5PT 0PT 4.5PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Dividends
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:13.5PT 0PT 4.5PT;TEXT-INDENT:27PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	In December&nbsp;2012, the Company&#x2019;s Board of Directors approved the initiation of an annual cash dividend program in the amount of $0.10 per share. In 2014, the Company&#x2019;s Board of Directors approved an increase in the annual dividend payment from $0.10 per share to $0.12 per share. In 2015, the Company&#x2019;s Board of Directors approved an increase in the annual dividend payment from $0.12 to $0.20 per share, to be paid semi-annually.&nbsp;&nbsp;Subsequent to fiscal 2015, the Company&#x2019;s Board of Directors approved an increase in the annual dividend to $0.26 per share, to be paid semi-annually. The Company&#x2019;s dividend policy is reviewed periodically by the Board of Directors. The amount and timing of all dividend payments is subject to the discretion of the Board of Directors and will depend upon business conditions, contractual obligations, legal restrictions, results of operations, financial conditions and other factors.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:13.5PT 0PT 4.5PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Property and Equipment, Net
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:4.5PT 0PT 0PT;TEXT-INDENT:24.5PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	Property and equipment are recorded at cost. Depreciation is calculated to amortize the depreciable assets over their useful lives using the straight-line method and commences when the asset is placed in service. The range of estimated useful lives is three to
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	ten
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	years. Leasehold improvements are amortized on a straight-line basis over the term of the lease or the estimated useful life of the improvement, whichever is shorter. Expenditures for repairs and maintenance are charged to expense as incurred. Expenditures for betterments and major improvements are capitalized. The carrying amount of assets sold or retired and related accumulated depreciation are removed from the balance sheet in the year of disposal and any resulting gains or losses are included in the
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	consolidated
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	statements of operations.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:9PT 0PT 0PT;TEXT-INDENT:24.5PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
</P>
<P>
<FONT SIZE="1">
</FONT>
</P>
<DIV STYLE="WIDTH:100%">
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	37
</FONT>
</P>
</DIV>
<HR SIZE="3" STYLE="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">
</HR>
<P STYLE="PAGE-BREAK-AFTER:ALWAYS">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<A NAME="eolPage38"></A>
<DIV STYLE="WIDTH:100%">
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	THE HACKETT GROUP, INC.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	NOTES TO CONSOLIDATED FINANCIAL STATEMENTS
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	1. Basis of Presentation and General Information (continued)
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
	&nbsp;
</P>
</DIV>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:9PT 0PT 0PT;TEXT-INDENT:24.5PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	The Company capitalizes the costs of internal-use software, which generally includes hardware, software, and payroll-related costs for employees who are directly associated with, and who devote time, to the development of internal-use computer software
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:13.5PT 0PT 4.5PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Long-Lived Assets (excluding Goodwill and Other Intangible Assets)
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:4.5PT 0PT 0PT;TEXT-INDENT:24.5PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	Long-lived assets are reviewed for impairment whenever events or circumstances indicate that the carrying amount of an asset may not be fully recoverable. If an evaluation is required, the estimated future undiscounted cash flows associated with the asset are compared to the asset&#x2019;s carrying amount to determine if there has been an impairment. The amount of an impairment is calculated as the difference between the fair value of the asset and its carrying value. Estimates of future undiscounted cash flows are based on management&#x2019;s view of growth rates for the related business, anticipated future economic conditions and estimates of residual values.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:13.5PT 0PT 0PT 12.2PT;TEXT-INDENT: -12.2PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Business Combinations
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:4.5PT 0PT 0PT;TEXT-INDENT:27PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	For transactions that are considered business combinations, the Company utilizes
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	fair values in determining the carrying values of the purchased assets and assumed liabilities, which are recorded at fair value at acquisition date, and identifiable intangible assets are recorded at fair value. Costs directly related to the business combinations are recorded as expenses as they are incurred. Fair values are subject to refinement for up to one year after the closing date of an acquisition as information relative to closing date fair values become available. A bargain purchase gain on an acquisition occurs when the net of the estimated fair value of the assets acquired and liabilities assumed exceeds the consideration paid.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:13.5PT 0PT 0PT;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Goodwill and Other Intangible Assets
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:4.5PT 0PT 0PT;TEXT-INDENT:24.5PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	Goodwill and intangible assets deemed to have indefinite lives are not amortized, but rather are tested for impairment on an annual basis, or more frequently if events or changes in circumstances indicate potential impairment. Finite-lived intangible assets are amortized over their useful lives. The excess cost of the acquisition over the fair value of the net assets acquired is recorded as goodwill.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:9PT 0PT 0PT;TEXT-INDENT:24.5PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	Goodwill is tested at least annually for impairment at the reporting unit level utilizing the market
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	approach
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	. The reporting units consist of The Hackett Group (including Benchmarking, Business Transformation, Business Transformation Enterprise Performance Management (&#x201C;EPM&#x201D;), Strategy and Operations and Executive Advisory Programs) and Hackett Technology Solutions (including SAP ERP
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	and SAP Application Maintenance and Support (&#x201C;AMS&#x201D;)
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	, Oracle EPM
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	and
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	EPM
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	AMS
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	)
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	. In assessing the recoverability of goodwill and intangible assets, the Company utilizes the market approach and makes estimates based on assumptions regarding various factors to determine if impairment tests are met. The market approach utilizes valuation multiples based on operating data from publicly traded companies within the same industry. Multiples derived from guideline companies provide an indication of how much a knowledgeable investor in the marketplace would be willing to pay for a company. These multiples are then applied to the Company&#x2019;s reporting units to arrive at an indication of value. This approach contains management&#x2019;s judgment, using appropriate and customary assumptions available at the time.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:9PT 0PT 0PT;TEXT-INDENT:24.5PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	The Company performed its annual
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	step one
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	impairment test of goodwill in the fou
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	rth quarter of fiscal years
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	2015 and
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	2014
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	and determined that goodwill was not impaired. The carrying amount and activity of goodwill attributable to The Hackett Group and Hackett Technology Solutions was as follows (in thousands):
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 1PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 1PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">

</FONT>
</P>

<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 1PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&nbsp;

<P STYLE="MARGIN:9PT 0PT 0PT;TEXT-INDENT:24.5PT;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	Other intangible assets are tested for potential impairment whenever events or changes in circumstances suggest that the carrying value of an asset may not be fully recoverable. If an evaluation is required, the estimated future undiscounted cash flows associated with the asset are compared to the asset&#x2019;s carrying amount to determine if there has been an impairment. The amount of an impairment is calculated as the difference between the fair value of the asset and its carrying value. Estimates of future undiscounted cash flows are based on management&#x2019;s view of growth rates for the related business, anticipated future economic conditions and estimates of residual values. Other intangible assets arise from business combinations and consist of customer relationships, customer backlog
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	and trademarks that are amortized on a straight-line or accelerated basis over periods of up to five years.
</FONT>
</P>

</P>

<P STYLE="MARGIN:0.05PT 0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
	&nbsp;
</P>
</TD>
<TD VALIGN="BOTTOM" STYLE="WIDTH:01.64%;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-LEFT:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-RIGHT:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;PADDING:0PT;">

	&nbsp;
</P>
</TD>

<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 1PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:9PT 0PT 0PT;TEXT-INDENT:24.5PT;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	All of the Company&#x2019;s intangible assets are expected to be fully amortized by the end of 2018.&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	For the year ended January 1, 2016, the Company
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	recorded $2.2 million of amortization expense.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	The estimated future amortization expense of intangible assets as of January
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	1
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	, 201
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	6
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	is as follows: $1.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	1
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	million in 2016
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	, $1.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	3
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	million in 2017 and $1.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	4
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	million in 2018.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	See Note 15
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	for further discussion.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:13.5PT 0PT 0PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Revenue Recognition
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:4.5PT 0PT 0PT;TEXT-INDENT:24.5PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	Revenue is principally derived from fees for services generated on a project-by-project basis
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	Revenue for services rendered is recognized on a time and materials basis or on a fixed-fee or capped-fee basis.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:9PT 0PT 0PT;TEXT-INDENT:24.5PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	Revenue for time and materials contracts is recognized based on the number of hours worked by our consultants at an agreed upon rate per hour and is recognized in the period in which services are performed.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:9PT 0PT 0PT;TEXT-INDENT:24.5PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	Revenue related to fixed-fee or capped-fee contracts is recognized on the proportional performance method of accounting based on the ratio of labor hours incurred to estimated total labor hours. This percentage is multiplied by the contracted dollar amount of the project to determine the amount of revenue to recognize in an accounting period. The contracted dollar amount used in this calculation excludes the amount the client pays for reimbursable expenses. There are situations where the number of hours to complete projects may exceed the original estimate. These increases can be as a result of an increase in project scope, unforeseen events that arise, or the inability of the client or the delivery team to fulfill their responsibilities. On an on-going basis, project delivery, Office of Risk Management and finance personnel review hours incurred and estimated total labor hours to complete projects. Any revisions in these estimates are reflected in the period in which they become known. If the Company estimates indicate that a contract loss will occur, a loss provision will be recorded in the period in which the loss first becomes probable and reasonably estimable. Contract losses are determined to be the amount by which the estimated direct costs of the contract exceed the estimated total revenue that will be generated by the contract and are included in total cost of service.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:9PT 0PT 0PT;TEXT-INDENT:24.5PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	Revenue from advisory services is recognized ratably over the life of the agreements.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:9PT 0PT 0PT;TEXT-INDENT:24.5PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	Additionally, the Company earns revenue from the resale of software licenses and maintenance contracts. Revenue for the resale software and software licenses is recognized upon contract execution and customer receipt of software. Revenue from maintenance contracts is recognized ratably over the life of the agreements.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:9PT 0PT 0PT;TEXT-INDENT:24.5PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	Revenue for contracts with multiple elements is allocated based on the
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	respective
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	selling price of the
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	individual
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	elements.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:9PT 0PT 0PT;TEXT-INDENT:24.5PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	Unbilled revenue represents revenue for services performed that have not been invoiced. If the Company does not accurately estimate the scope of the work to be performed, or does not manage its projects properly within the planned periods of time, or does not meet clients
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&#x2019;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	expectations under the contracts, then future consulting margins may be negatively affected or losses on existing contracts may need to be recognized. Any such reductions in margins or contract losses could be material to the Company&#x2019;s results of operations.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:9PT 0PT 0PT;TEXT-INDENT:24.5PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	Sales tax collected from customers and remitted to the applicable taxing authorities is accounted for on a net basis, with no impact on revenue.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:9PT 0PT 0PT;TEXT-INDENT:24.5PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	Revenue before reimbursements excludes reimbursable expenses charged to clients. Reimbursements, which include travel and out-of-pocket expenses, are included in revenue, and an equivalent amount of reimbursable expenses is included in cost of service.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:9PT 0PT 0PT;TEXT-INDENT:24.5PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
</P>
<P>
<FONT SIZE="1">
</FONT>
</P>
<DIV STYLE="WIDTH:100%">
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">

<A NAME="eolPage40"></A>
<DIV STYLE="WIDTH:100%">
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	THE HACKETT GROUP, INC.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	NOTES TO CONSOLIDATED FINANCIAL STATEMENTS
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	1. Basis of Presentation and General Information (continued)
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
	&nbsp;
</P>
</DIV>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:9PT 0PT 0PT;TEXT-INDENT:24.5PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	The agreements entered into in connection with a project, whether time and materials based or fixed-fee or capped-fee based, typically allow clients to terminate early due to breach or for convenience with 30 days&#x2019; notice. In the event of termination, the client is contractually required to pay for all time, materials and expenses incurred by the Company through the effective date of the termination. In addition, from time to time the Company enters into agreements with its clients that limit its right to enter into business relationships with specific competitors of that client for a specific time period. These provisions typically prohibit the Company from performing a defined range of services which it might otherwise be willing to perform for potential clients. These provisions are generally limited to six to twelve months and usually apply only to specific employees or the specific project team.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:13.5PT 0PT 0PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Stock Based Compensation
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:4.5PT 0PT 0PT;TEXT-INDENT:24.5PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	The Company recognizes compensation expense for awards of equity instruments to employees based on the grant-date fair value of those awards, with limited exceptions, over the requisite service period.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:13.5PT 0PT 0PT 12.2PT;TEXT-INDENT: -12.2PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Restructuring Reserves
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:4.5PT 0PT 0PT;TEXT-INDENT:27PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	Restructuring reserves reflect judgments and estimates of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	the Company&#x2019;s
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	ultimate costs of severance, closure and consolidation of facilities and settlement of contractual obligations under
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	its
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	operating leases, including sublease rental rates, absorption period to sublease s
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	pace and other related costs. The Company
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	reassess
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	es
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	the reserve requirements to complete each individual plan under
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	the
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	restructuring programs at the end of each reporting period. If these estimates change in the future or actual results differ from
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	the Company&#x2019;s
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	estimates, additional charges
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	may be required
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	. &nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:13.5PT 0PT 0PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Income Taxes
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:4.5PT 0PT 0PT;TEXT-INDENT:24.5PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	Deferred
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	tax assets and liabilities are determined based on differences between the financial reporting carrying values and tax bases of assets and liabilities, and are measured by using enacted tax rates expected to apply to taxable income in the years in which those differences are expected to reverse. Deferred income taxes also reflect the impact of certain state operating loss and tax credit carryforwards. A valuation allowance is provided if the Company believes it is more likely than not that all or some portion of the deferred tax asset will not be realized. An increase or decrease in the valuation allowance, if any, that results from a change in circumstances, and which causes a change in the Company&#x2019;s judgment about the realizability of the related deferred tax asset, is included in the tax provision.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:9PT 0PT 0PT;TEXT-INDENT:24.5PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	The
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	Company
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	utilized
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	a more-likely-than-not threshold for financial statement recognition and measurement of a tax position taken or expected to be taken in a tax return. This interpretation also provides guidance on de-recognition of income tax assets and liabilities, classification of current and deferred income tax assets and liabilities, accounting for interest and penalties associated with tax positions, accounting for income taxes in interim periods and income tax disclosures. The Company reports penalties and tax-related interest expense as a component of income tax expense.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:13.5PT 0PT 0PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Net Income per Common Share
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:4.5PT 0PT 0PT;TEXT-INDENT:24.5PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	Basic net income per common share is computed by dividing net income by the weighted average number of common shares outstanding during the period. With regard to common stock subject to vesting requirements and restricted stock units issued to employees, the calculation includes only the vested portion of such stock.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:9PT 0PT 0PT;TEXT-INDENT:24.5PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	The potential issuance of common shares upon the exercise, conversion or vesting of unvested restricted stock units, common stock subject to vesting, stock options and stock appreciation right units ("SARs"), as calculated under the treasury stock method, may be dilutive.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	Diluted net income per share is computed by dividing the net income by the weighted average number of common shares outstanding, and will increase by the assumed conversion of other potentially dilutive securities during the period.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:9PT 0PT 0PT;TEXT-INDENT:24.5PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	The following table reconciles basic and diluted weighted average shares:
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;LINE-HEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 1PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>

<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	NOTES TO CONSOLIDATED FINANCIAL STATEMENTS
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">

</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	1. Basis of Presentation and General Information (continued)
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
	&nbsp;
</P>
</DIV>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:9PT 0PT 0PT;TEXT-INDENT:24.5PT;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	There were
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	0.5 million,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	0.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	3
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&nbsp;million and
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	0.8
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&nbsp;million
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	shares of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	underlying
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	awards granted excluded from the above reconci
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	liation for the years ended
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	2015,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	2014
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	and
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	201
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	3
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	, respectively, as their inclusion would have had an anti-dilutive effect on dilu
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	ted net income per share.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:13.5PT 0PT 0PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Fair Value of Financial Instruments
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:4.5PT 0PT 0PT;TEXT-INDENT:24.5PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	The Company&#x2019;s financial instruments consis
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	t of cash and cash equivalents
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	, accounts receivable and unbilled revenue, accounts payable, accrued expenses and other liabilities and debt. As of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	January 1, 2016
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	and
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	January 2, 2015
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	the carrying amount of each financial instrument, with the exception of debt, approximated the instrument&#x2019;s fair value due to the short-term nature and maturity of these instruments.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:9PT 0PT 0PT;TEXT-INDENT:24.5PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	The Company uses significant other observable market data or assumptions (Level 2 inputs as defined in accounting guidance) that it believes market participants would use in pricing debt. The fair value of the debt approximated its carrying amount using Level 2 inputs, due to the short-term variable interest rates based on market rates utilizing the market approach.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:13.5PT 0PT 0PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Concentration of Credit Risk
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:4.5PT 0PT 0PT;TEXT-INDENT:24.5PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	The Company provides services primarily to Global 2000 companies and other sophisticated buyers of business consulting and information technology services. The Company performs ongoing credit evaluations of its major customers and maintains reserves for potential credit losses. In
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	2015,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	201
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	4 and
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	201
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	3
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	no customer accounted for more than 5% of total revenue.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:13.5PT 0PT 0PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Management&#x2019;s Estimates
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:4.5PT 0PT 0PT;TEXT-INDENT:24.5PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	The preparation of financial statements in conformity with
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	U.S.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	GAAP requires management to make estimates and assumptions that affect the reported amounts of assets and liabilities and disclosure of contingent assets and liabilities as of the date of the financial statements and the reported amounts of revenue and expenses during the reporting period. Actual results could differ from those estimates.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:13.5PT 0PT 0PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Other Comprehensive Income
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:4.5PT 0PT 0PT;TEXT-INDENT:24.5PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	The Company reports its comprehensive income in accordance with FASB ASC Topic 220,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Comprehensive Income,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	which establishes standards for reporting and presenting comprehensive income and its components in a full set of financial statements. Other comprehensive income consists of net income and cumulative currency translation adjustments.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:13.5PT 0PT 0PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Translation of Non-U.S. Currency Amounts
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:4.5PT 0PT 0PT;TEXT-INDENT:24.5PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	The assets and liabilities held by the Company&#x2019;s foreign entities that have a functional currency other than the U.S.&nbsp;Dollar are translated into U.S. Dollars at exchange rates in effect at the end of each reporting period. Foreign entity revenue and expenses are translated into U.S. Dollars at the average rates that prevailed during the period. The resulting net translation gains and losses are reported as foreign currency translation adjustments in shareholders&#x2019; equity as a component of accumulated other comprehensive income. Gains and losses from foreign currency transactions are included in net income.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:13.5PT 0PT 0PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Segment Reporting
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:4.5PT 0PT 0PT;TEXT-INDENT:24.5PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	The Company engages in business activities in one operating segment, which provides business and technology consulting services.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:13.5PT 0PT 0PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Recent Accounting Pronouncements
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:9PT 0PT 0PT;TEXT-INDENT:23.75PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	In May 2014, the FASB issued guidance on revenue recognition, which provides for a single, principles-based model for revenue recognition and replaces the existing revenue recognition guidance. The guidance is effective for annual and interim periods beginning on or after
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	December 15, 2017
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	and will replace most existing revenue recognition guidance under U.S. GAAP when it becomes effective. It permits the use of either a retrospective or cumulative effect transition method and early adoption is permitted
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	, however not before December 15, 2016
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	. The Company has not yet selected a transition method and is in the process of evaluating the effect this standard will have on its consolidated financial statements and related disclosures.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:6PT 0PT 0PT;TEXT-INDENT:27PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	In April 2015, the FASB issued amendments to
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	its guidance
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	which are intended to simplify the balance sheet presentation of debt issuance costs. These amendments require that debt issuance costs related to a recognized debt liability be presented in the balance sheet as a direct deduction from the carrying amount of the debt liability, consistent with debt discounts. The recognition and measurement guidance for debt issuance costs are not affected by this update. The amendments are effective for annual and interim periods beginning after December 15, 2015 and requires a retrospective transition method. Early adoption is permitted for financial
</FONT>
</P>
<P>
<FONT SIZE="1">
</FONT>
</P>

	&nbsp;

<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">

	1. Basis of Presentation and General Information (continued)
</FONT>

</DIV>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:6PT 0PT 0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	statements that have not been previously issued. The Company does not expect the adoption to have a material impact on its consolidated financial statements.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:6PT 0PT 0PT;TEXT-INDENT:27PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	On November 20, 2015, the FASB issued guidance which requires an entity to present all deferred tax assets and liabilities as non-current in a classified balance sheet. The update becomes effective January 1, 2017, however early adoption is permitted. The Company chose early adoption for the periods presented.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;LINE-HEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<A NAME="HCKT-20160101X10K_HTM_P259643946">
</A>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:27PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	In February 2016, the FASB issued guidance on leases which supersedes the current lease guidance
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	. The core principle requires lessees to recognize the assets and liabilities that arise from nearly all leases in the statement of financial position. Accounting applied by lessors will remain largely consistent with previous guidance, additional changes set to align lessor accounting with the revised lessee model and the FASB&#x2019;s revenue recognition guidance. The amendments are effective for fiscal years beginning after December 15, 2018, including interim periods within those fiscal years. Early adoption is permitted. The Company is currently assessing the impact of this standard on its consolidated financial statements.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:13.5PT 0PT 0PT;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">

<P STYLE="MARGIN:9PT 0PT 0PT;TEXT-INDENT:27PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">

	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;LINE-HEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 1PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 1PT">
<A NAME="HCKT-20160101X10K_HTM_FN3">
</A>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;COLOR:#000000;">
	2. Fair Value Measurement
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:4.5PT 0PT 0PT;TEXT-INDENT:24.5PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	The Company records its assets and liabilities in accordance with FASB ASC Topic 820,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;COLOR:#000000;">
	Fair Value Measurements and Disclosures
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	(&#x201C;ASC 820&#x201D;). ASC 820 defines fair value as the exchange price that would be received for an asset or paid to transfer a liability (exit price) in the principal or most advantageous market for the asset or liability in an orderly transaction between market participants on the measurement date. ASC 820 also establishes a fair value hierarchy which requires an entity to maximize the use of observable inputs and minimize the use of unobservable inputs when measuring fair value. ASC 820 describes the following three levels of inputs that may be used to measure fair value:
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:9PT 0PT 0PT;TEXT-INDENT:24.5PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	Level 1: Quoted market prices in active markets for identical assets or liabilities
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:9PT 0PT 0PT;TEXT-INDENT:24.5PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	Level 2: Observable market-based inputs or unobservable inputs that are corroborated by market data
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:9PT 0PT 0PT;TEXT-INDENT:24.5PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	Level 3: Unobservable inputs that are not corroborated by market data
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:13.5PT 0PT 0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;COLOR:#000000;">
	3.
</FONT>
<A NAME="HCKT-20160101X10K_HTM_FN4">
</A>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;COLOR:#000000;">
	Accounts Receivable and Unbilled Revenue, Net
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:4.5PT 0PT 0PT;TEXT-INDENT:24.5PT;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	Accounts receivable and unbilled revenue, net, consists of the following (in thousands):
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:24.5PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 1PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>

<P STYLE="MARGIN:0.05PT 0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 8PT">

	January 1,

</P>
</TD>
<TD VALIGN="BOTTOM" STYLE="WIDTH:01.66%;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-LEFT:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-RIGHT:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BACKGROUND-COLOR: #AUTO;PADDING:0PT;">
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0.05PT 0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
	&nbsp;
</P>
</TD>

<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:13.5PT 0PT 0PT;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	7
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	. Restructuring Costs
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:9PT 0PT 0PT;TEXT-INDENT:22.5PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	During 2014, the Company recorded restructuring costs of $3.6 million, primarily for reductions in consultants and functional support personnel in Europe. These actions were taken as a result of the continued decline in demand in the Company&#x2019;s European markets. The Company
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	took steps
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	to redu
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	ce its costs to better align its
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	overall cost structure and organization
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	with anticipated demand for its
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	services.
</FONT>
</P>

<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	On February&nbsp;21, 2012, the Compan
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	y entered into a credit agreement
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	with Bank o
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	f America, N.A. Under the c
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	redit

<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	agreement

<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">

</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	$20.0
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	million pursuant to a revolving line of credit (the &#x201C;Revolver&#x201D;) and up to
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	$30.0
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	million pursuant to a term loan (the &#x201C;Term Loan,&#x201D; and together with the Revolver, the &#x201C;Credit Facility&#x201D;).
</FONT>
</P>

<P STYLE="MARGIN:10PT 0PT 0PT;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<A NAME="HCKT-20160101X10K_HTM_FN11">
</A>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	9
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	. Income Taxes
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:4.5PT 0PT 0PT;TEXT-INDENT:24.5PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	The Company files federal income tax returns, as well as multiple state, local and foreign jurisdiction tax returns. A number of years may elapse before an uncertain tax position is audited and finally resolved. While it is often difficult to predict the final outcome or the timing of resolution on any particular uncertain tax position, the Company believes that its reserves for income taxes reflect the most probable outcome. The Company adjusts these reserves, as well as the related interest, in light of changing facts and circumstances. The resolution of a matter would be recognized as an adjustment to the provision for income taxes and the effective tax rate in the period of resolution. The Company is no longer subject to examinations of its federal income tax returns by the Internal Revenu
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	e Service for years through 2011
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	and all significant state, local and foreign matters have been c
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	oncluded for years
</FONT>
<BR />
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	through 2011
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	.
</FONT>
</P>

<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 1PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:9PT 0PT 0PT;TEXT-INDENT:24.5PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	As of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	January 1
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	, 2016, the Company had
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	$2.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	3
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	million of U.S. state net operating loss carryforwards. Additionally, at
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	January 1
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	, 2016, the Company had
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	$7.6
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	million of foreign net operating loss carryforwards, of which
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	$3.1
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	million related to operations in the U.K.,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	$1.1
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	million related to operations in France and
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	$0.5
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	million related to operations in Germany. A significant amount of the foreign net operating losses may be carried forward indefinitely.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:9PT 0PT 0PT;TEXT-INDENT:24.5PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	The liability method of accounting for deferred income taxes requires a valuation allowance against deferred tax assets if, based on the weight of available evidence, it is more likely than not that some or all of the deferred tax assets will not be realized. In determining the need for valuation allowances the Company considers evidence such as history of losses and general economic conditions. At January 1, 2016 and January 2, 2015, the Company had a valuation
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	allowance of $1.3 million and
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	$1.5 million
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	, respectively,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	to reduce deferred income tax assets primarily related to foreign and state net operating loss and tax credit carryforwards.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:9PT 0PT 0PT;TEXT-INDENT:24.5PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	The undistributed earnings in foreign subsidiaries of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	approximately
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	$2.5
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	million are permanently invested abroad and will not be repatriated to the U.S. in the foreseeable future. Because they are considered to be indefinitely reinvested, no U.S. federal or state deferred income taxes have been provided on these earnings. Upon distribution of those earnings, in the form of dividends or otherwise, the Company would be subject to both U.S. income taxes (subject to an adjustment for foreign tax credits) and withholding taxes payable to the various foreign countries in which it operates. Because of the availability of U.S. foreign tax credits, it is not practicable to determine the U.S. foreign income tax liability that would be payable if such earnings were not reinvested indefinitely.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:9PT 0PT 0PT;TEXT-INDENT:24.5PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	Penalties and tax-related interest expense are reported as a component of income tax expense. For the years ended January 1, 2016 and January 2, 2015 the total amount of accrued income tax-related interest and penalties was
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	$20
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	2
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	thousand and
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	$357
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	thousand, respectively.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:9PT 0PT 0PT;TEXT-INDENT:24.5PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	The
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	Company prescribes a more-likely-than-not threshold for financial statement recognition and measurement of a tax position taken or expected to be taken in a tax return. This interpretation also provides guidance on de-recognition of income tax assets and liabilities, classification of current and deferred income tax assets and liabilities, accounting for interest and penalties associated with tax positions, accounting for income taxes in interim periods and income tax disclosures.
</FONT>
</P>

<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	The number of shares available for future issuance under the
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	Company's stock
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">

	Stock Options
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	and SARs
</FONT>

<P STYLE="MARGIN:4.5PT 0PT 0PT;TEXT-INDENT:24.5PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	The Company has granted stock options to employees and directors of the Company at exercise prices equal to the market value of the stock at the date of grant. The options generally vest ratably over
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	four
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	years, based on continued employment, with a maximum term of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	ten
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	years.
</FONT>

<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	On February 8, 2012, the Compensation Committee approved the fiscal year 2012 through 2015 equity compensation target for the Chief Executive Officer and Chief Operating Officer. Under this target, a single performance-based option grant was made to the Company&#x2019;s Chief Executive Officer and the Chief Operating Officer of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	1,912,500
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	options and
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	1,004,063
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	options, respectively, totaling
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	2,916,563
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	options
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	, each with an exercise price of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	$4.00
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	and a fair value of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	$1.31
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	. &nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	One
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	-half of the options vest upon the achievement of at least
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	50%
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	growth of pro forma earnings per share and the remaining half vest upon the achievement of at least
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	50%
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	pro forma EBITDA growth
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	. &nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	Pro forma EBITDA is defined as pro forma earnings before interest, taxes and depreciation. Each
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	metric can be achieved at any time during the
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	six
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	-year term of the award based on a trailing
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	twelve
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	month period measured quarterly. The grants will expire if neither target is achieved during the six-year term. The base year for the performance calculation is fiscal 2011 for both pro forma earnings per share and pro forma EBITDA performance targets.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:9PT 0PT 0PT;TEXT-INDENT:24.5PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	In March of 2013
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	the performance-based stock option grants were surrendered by the Company&#x2019;s Chief Executive Officer and Chief Operating Officer and replaced with
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	SARs
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	, totaling
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	2,916,563
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	, equal in number to the number of options granted to each of them in 2012. The terms and conditions and the specific performance targets that must be achieved in order for the SAR
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	s to vest are the same as
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	those of the
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	surrendered options
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	, with the exception that the SARs will be settled in cash, stock or any combination thereof, at the Company&#x2019;s discretion.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:9PT 0PT 0PT;TEXT-INDENT:24.5PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	The SARs related to the pro forma EPS target were earned and vested in the first quarter of 2015 with the Audit Committee&#x2019;s approval of the Company&#x2019;s 2014 financial statements and the SARs related to the pro forma EBITDA target were earned and vested in the first quarter of 2016 with the Audit Committee&#x2019;s approval of the Company&#x2019;s 2015 financial statements. As of January 1, 2016,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	no
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	SARs had been exercised.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:9PT 0PT 0PT;TEXT-INDENT:24.5PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	In addition,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	470,000
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	vested stock options were surrendered and replaced with SARs
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	with an extended life
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	during 2013
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	.&nbsp;&nbsp;Subsequently,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	in 2014,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	the extended life
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	of the SARS
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	was rescinded and the
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	SARS expired
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	unexercised
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	. &nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:9PT 0PT 0PT;TEXT-INDENT:24.5PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	SAR
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	activity for the year ended

<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">

<P STYLE="MARGIN:9PT 0PT 0PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Restricted Stock Units
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:4.5PT 0PT 0PT;TEXT-INDENT:24.5PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	Under the stock plans, participants may be granted restricted
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	stock units, each of which represents a conditional right to receive a common share in the future. The restricted stock units granted under this plan generally vest over one of the following vesting schedules: (1)&nbsp;a
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	four
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	-year period, with
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	50%
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	vesting on the second anniversary and
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	25%
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	of the shares vesting on the third and
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	fourth
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	anniversaries of the grant date, (2)&nbsp;a
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	four
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	-year period, with
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	25%
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	vesting on the first,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	second
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	, &nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	third
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	and
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	fourth
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	anniversary, or (3)&nbsp;a
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	three
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	-year period with
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	33%
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	vesting on the first,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	second
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	and
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	third
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	anniversary. Upon vesting, the restricted stock units will convert into an equivalent number of shares of common stock. The amount of expense relating to the restricted stock units is based on the closing market price of the Company&#x2019;s common stock on the date of grant and is amortized on a straight-line basis over the applicable requisite service period. Restricted stock unit activity for the year ended
</FONT>

	January

</A>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Tender Offer
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:4.5PT 0PT 0PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	On August 28, 2013, the Company announced a tender offer to purchase up to
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	$35.75
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	million in value of shares of its common stock,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	$0.001
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	par value per share, at a price not greater than
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	$6.50
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	nor less than
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	$5.75
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	per share, to the seller in cash, less any applicable
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	withholding taxes and without interest (the "Offer"). On September 26, 2013, the Company amended
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	the Offer (the "Amended Offer"
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	)
</FONT>
</P>

	to increase the price range at which it would purchas

	$6.9
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	million, excluding fees and expenses related to the Amended Offer. The 1.0 million shares represented approximately
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	3%
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	of the Company's issued and outstanding shares of common stock at that time. The Company financed the Amended Offer from borrowings under the Amended Term Loan under its existing Credit Facility. See Note 8 for further detail.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:9PT 0PT 0PT 12.25PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Employee Stock Purchase Plan
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:4.5PT 0PT 0PT;TEXT-INDENT:27.35PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	Effective July&nbsp;1, 1998, the Company adopted an Employee Stock Purchase Plan to provide substantially all employees who have completed
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	three
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	months of service as of the beginning of an offering period an opportunity to purchase shares of its common stock through payroll deductions. Purchases on any one grant are limited to
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	10%
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	of eligible compensation. Shares of the Company&#x2019;s common stock may be purchased by employees at
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	six
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	-month intervals at
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	95%
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	of the fair market value on the last trading day of each six-month period. The aggregate fair market value, determined as of the first trading date of the offering period, of shares purchased by an employee may not exceed
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	$25,000
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	annually. The Employee Stock Purchase Plan expires on
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	July&nbsp;1, 2018
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	. A total of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	4,275,000
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	shares of common stock are available for purchase under the plan with a limit of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	400,000
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	shares of common stock to be issued per offering period. For plan years
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	2015,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	2014,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	and
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	2013,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	48,356
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	shares,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	94,333
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	shares and
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	113,905
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	shares, respectively, were issued.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:9PT 0PT 0PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">

<P STYLE="MARGIN:4.5PT 0PT 0PT;TEXT-INDENT:24.5PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	On February&nbsp;13, 2004, the Company&#x2019;s Board of Directors adopted a Shareholder Rights Plan. Under the Plan, a dividend of one preferred share purchase right (a &#x201C;Right&#x201D;) was declared for each share of common stock of the Company that was outstanding on February&nbsp;26, 2004.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:9PT 0PT 0PT;TEXT-INDENT:24.5PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">

	T

<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	he Rights had
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">

</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	have
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">

</FONT>

</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	ed
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	to acquire a significant interest in the Company on terms not approved by the Board of Directors.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	The Rights expired on February&nbsp;13, 2014.

<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	12
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	. Benefit Plan
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:4.5PT 0PT 0PT;TEXT-INDENT:27.35PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	The Company maintains a 401(k) plan covering all eligible employees. Subject to certain dollar limits, eligible employees may contribute up to
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	15%
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	of their pre-tax annual compensation to the plan. The Company may make discretionary contributions on an annual basis. During fiscal years
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	2015
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	, &nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	2014
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	and
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	2013
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	, the Company made matching contributions of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	25%
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	of employee contributions up to
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	4%
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	of their gross salaries. The Company&#x2019;s matching contributions were
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	$0.3
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	million for each of the fiscal years ended
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	January 1, 2016, January 2, 2015 and
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	December 27, 2013.
</FONT>

<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<A NAME="HCKT-20160101X10K_HTM_FN15">

<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	13
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	. Transactions with Related Parties

<P STYLE="MARGIN:4.5PT 0PT 0PT;TEXT-INDENT:27.35PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	There were
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	no
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	relate
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	d party transactions in

	201

<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
