<P STYLE="MARGIN:13.5PT 0PT 0PT;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<A NAME="HCKT-20160101X10K_HTM_FN16">
</A>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	14
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	. Litigation
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:4.5PT 0PT 0PT;TEXT-INDENT:24.5PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	The Company is involved in legal proceedings, claims, and litigation arising in the ordinary course of business not specifically discussed herein. In the opinion of management, the final disposition of such matters will not have a material adverse effect on the Company&#x2019;s consolidated financial position, cash flows or results of operations.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:13.5PT 0PT 0PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	15
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	. Acquisition
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:4.5PT 0PT 0PT;TEXT-INDENT:24.5PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	During the quarter ended March 28, 2014, the Company acquired the U.S., Canada and Uruguay operations of Technolab International Corporation ("Technolab")
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	, an EPM AMS business
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	. &nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:9PT 0PT 5PT;TEXT-INDENT:24.5PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	At closing, the
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	s
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	eller received
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	$3.0
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	million in cash, not subject to vesting, and
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	$1.0
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	million in shares subject to vesting, which is being recorded as non-cash compensation over the service vesting period. The
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	s
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	eller also had the ability to earn an additional
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	$8.0
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	million in a combination of cash, not subject to service vesting, and stock, subject to service vesting, based on a one-year profitability-based earn-out contingent upon actual results achieved. The entire cash portion of the earn-out was recorded as compensation expense in 2014. The stock portion of the earn-out is being recorded as compensation expense over the service vesting period. During the third quarter of 2015, the Company settled the contingent earn-out with cash and stock issuances in accordance with the agreement.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:24.5PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	The purchase accounting resulted in a bargain purchase gain of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	$3.0
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	million on the acquisition and intangible assets with definite lives of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	$7.7
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	million which will be amortized over periods ranging from
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	2
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	years to
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	5
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	years.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:9PT 0PT 0PT;TEXT-INDENT:24.5PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">

</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	values (in thousands):

</P>

	approximately
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">

<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	Pro forma results of Technolab have not been presented as the acquisition closed at the beginning of 2014 and therefore, the full year results of Technolab are included in the Company&#x2019;s consolidated financial results. Technolab contributed total revenue of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	$10.3
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	million and contribution before depreciation, amortization, interest, corporate overhead allocation and taxes of

	$3.3

<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	million.

<EFX_PART_II>
<A NAME="FIS_PART_II_2"></A>
<EFX_ACCOUNTING_CHANGES>
<A NAME="FIS_ACCOUNTING_CHANGES"></A>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 0PT 55.45PT;TEXT-INDENT: -55.45PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<A NAME="HCKT-20160101X10K_HTM_ITEM9">
</A>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	ITEM&nbsp;9
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	. &nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;TEXT-INDENT:0PT;MARGIN-LEFT:0PT;PADDING:0PT 37PT 0PT 0PT;">
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	CHANGES IN AND DISAGREEMENTS WITH ACCOUNTANTS ON ACCOUNTING AND FINANCIAL DISCLOSURE
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:12PT 0PT 0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<A NAME="HCKT-20160101X10K_HTM_ITEM9A">
</A>
<FONT STYLE="TEXT-INDENT:0PT;MARGIN-LEFT:0PT; PADDING-RIGHT:44.5PT;">
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="TEXT-INDENT:0PT;MARGIN-LEFT:0PT; PADDING-RIGHT:4PT;TEXT-ALIGN:LEFT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	On May 20, 2015, the Audit Committee of the Board of Directors of The Hackett Group, Inc. (the
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&#x201C;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	Company
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&#x201D;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	dismissed BDO USA, LLP (
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&#x201C;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	BDO
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&#x201D;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	) as the Company
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&#x2019;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	s independent registered public accounting firm, effective immediately.
</FONT>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:12PT 0PT 0PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;The audit reports of BDO on the consolidated financial statements of the Company as of and for the fiscal years ended January 2, 2015 and December 27, 2013 did not contain any adverse opinion or disclaimer of opinion, nor were they qualified or modified as to uncertainty, audit scope, or accounting principles.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:12PT 0PT 0PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	During the fiscal years ended January 2, 2015 and December 27, 2013, and through May 20, 2015, there were (i) no
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&#x201C;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	disagreements
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&#x201D;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	as that term is defined in Item 304(a)(1)(iv) of Regulation S-K and the related instructions, between the Company and BDO on any matter of accounting principles or practices, financial statement disclosure or auditing scope or procedure, which disagreements, if not resolved to the satisfaction of BDO, would have caused BDO to make reference to the subject matter of the disagreements in its reports on the financial statements for such years, except for the disagreement described below and (ii) no
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&#x201C;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	reportable events
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&#x201D;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	as that term is defined in Item 304(a)(1)(v) of Regulation S-K, except for the material weakness identified below.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:12PT 0PT 0PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="TEXT-INDENT:0PT;MARGIN-LEFT:0PT; PADDING-RIGHT:4PT;">
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="TEXT-INDENT:0PT;MARGIN-LEFT:0PT; PADDING-RIGHT:4PT;TEXT-ALIGN:LEFT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;As disclosed in the Company
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&#x2019;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	s Annual Report on Form 10-K for the fiscal year ended January 2, 2015 (the
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&#x201C;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	2014 Form 10-K
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&#x201D;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	), we acquired and accounted for certain assets and liabilities of Technolab International Corporation (
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&#x201C;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	Technolab
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&#x201D;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	) during the first quarter of 2014. No issues were raised regarding the Company
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&#x2019;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	s accounting for this transaction by BDO during BDO
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&#x2019;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	s initial review of the transaction during the first quarter. However, BDO
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&#x2019;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	s position changed subsequent to fiscal year-end during the course of its annual audit. The Company
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&#x2019;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	s management initially disagreed with the subsequent position taken by BDO related to the accounting for this transaction, but the Company ultimately accounted for the transaction in accordance with BDO
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&#x2019;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	s subsequent position. The Company
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&#x2019;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	s management concluded that the Company
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&#x2019;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	s internal control over financial reporting was effective as of the end of the period covered by the 2014 Form 10-K. However, BDO
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&#x2019;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	s report on management
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&#x2019;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	s assessment on the Company
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&#x2019;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	s internal control over financial reporting identified a material weakness specifically related to accounting for Technolab acquisition discussed above. The description of the material weakness identified by BDO and management
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&#x2019;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	s assessment of the Company
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&#x2019;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	s internal control over financial reporting contained in Item 9A of the 2014 Form 10-K are incorporated herein by reference. The Audit Committee discussed with BDO the disagreement over the accounting for the Technolab acquisition as well as the material weakness identified by BDO in its report. The Company has authorized BDO to respond fully to the inquiries of the successor independent registered accounting firm concerning the accounting for the Technolab acquisition and the related material weakness.
</FONT>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 12PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="TEXT-INDENT:0PT;MARGIN-LEFT:0PT; PADDING-RIGHT:4PT;">
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="TEXT-INDENT:0PT;MARGIN-LEFT:0PT; PADDING-RIGHT:4PT;TEXT-ALIGN:LEFT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	On May 22, 2015, following the conclusion of a competitive process managed by the Audit Committee, th
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	e Company engaged McGladrey LLP, now known as RSM US LLP (&#x201C;RSM&#x201D;),
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	as its independent registered public accounting firm for the fiscal year ending January 1, 2016. During the fiscal years ended January 2, 2015 and December 27, 2013 and through May 22, 2015, neither the Compan
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	y, nor anyone on its behalf, had
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	consulted
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	RSM
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	with respect to (i) the application of accounting principles to a specified transaction, either completed or proposed, or the type of audit opinion that might be rendered on the Company
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&#x2019;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	s consolidated financial statements, and neither a written report was provided to the Company nor oral advice was provided to the Company that
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	RSM
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	concluded was an important factor considered by the Company in reaching a decision as to the accounting, auditing or financial reporting issue; or (ii) any matter that was either the subject of a disagreement (as defined in Item 304(a)(1)(iv) of Regulation S-K and the related instructions) or a reportable event (as described in Item 304(a)(1)(v) of Regulation S-K).
</FONT>
</FONT>
</P>
</EFX_ACCOUNTING_CHANGES>
<EFX_CONTROL_AND_PROCEDURES>
<A NAME="FIS_CONTROL_AND_PROCEDURES"></A>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:13.5PT 0PT 0PT 55.05PT;TEXT-INDENT: -55.1PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	ITEM&nbsp; 9A
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;TEXT-INDENT:0PT;MARGIN-LEFT:0PT;PADDING:0PT 31PT 0PT 0PT;">
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	CONTROLS AND PROCEDURES
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:9PT 0PT 0PT;TEXT-INDENT:54PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	The Company maintains disclosure controls and procedures (&#x201C;DCP&#x201D;) that are designed to ensure that information required to be disclosed by us in reports that we file or submit under the Securities Exchange Act of 1934, as amended (&#x201C;the Exchange Act&#x201D;), is recorded, processed, summarized, and reported within the time periods specified in the SEC rules and forms, and that such information is accumulated and communicated to the Company&#x2019;s management, including its Chief Executive Officer (principal executive officer) and Chief Financial
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	Officer (principal financial officer), as appropriate, to allow for timely decisions regarding required disclosure.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:9PT 0PT 0PT;TEXT-INDENT:54PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	The Company, under the supervision and with the participation of the Comp
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	any&#x2019;s management, including the
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	Chief Executive
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	Officer and Chief Financial Officer, evaluated the effectiveness of the design and operation of the Company&#x2019;s DCP as of the end of the period covered by this report. Based on this evaluation, the Chief Executive Officer and the Chief Financial Officer concluded that our disclosure controls and procedures were effective as of the end of the period covered by the
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	Annual
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	Report on Form 10-
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	K
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;LINE-HEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;COLOR:#000000;">
	Changes in internal control over financial reporting
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:4.5PT 0PT 0PT;TEXT-INDENT:48.95PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	There were no changes in our internal control over financial reporting identified in connection with the evaluation required by paragraph (d)&nbsp;of Exchange Act Rules 13a-15 or 15d-15 that occurred during the three months ended January 1, 2016 that have materially affected, or are reasonably likely to materially affect, our internal control over financial reporting.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;LINE-HEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">

<EFX_AUDITORS_OPINION>
<A NAME="FIS_AUDITORS_OPINION_3"></A>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;LINE-HEIGHT:NORMAL;TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	REPORT OF INDEPENDENT REGISTERED PUBLIC ACCOUNTING FIRM
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;LINE-HEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;LINE-HEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;LINE-HEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	To the Board of Directors and Shareholders
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;LINE-HEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	The Hackett Group, Inc.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;LINE-HEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;LINE-HEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;LINE-HEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	We have audited The Hackett Group, Inc.'s internal control over financial reporting as of January 1, 2016, based on criteria established in
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;COLOR:#000000;">
	Internal Control &#x2014; Integrated Framework
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	issued by the Committee of Sponsoring Organizations of the Treadway Commission in 2013. The Hackett Group, Inc.&#x2019;s management is responsible for maintaining effective internal control over financial reporting and for its assessment of the effectiveness of internal control over financial reporting included in the accompanying Management&#x2019;s Report on Internal Control Over Financial Reporting. Our responsibility is to express an opinion on the company's internal control over financial reporting based on our audit.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;LINE-HEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;LINE-HEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	We conducted our audit in accordance with the standards of the Public Company Accounting Oversight Board (United States). Those standards require that we plan and perform the audit to obtain reasonable assurance about whether effective internal control over financial reporting was maintained in all material respects. Our audit included obtaining an understanding of internal control over financial reporting, assessing the risk that a material weakness exists, and testing and evaluating the design and operating effectiveness of internal control based on the assessed risk. Our audit also included performing such other procedures as we considered necessary in the circumstances. We believe that our audit provides a reasonable basis for our opinion.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;LINE-HEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;LINE-HEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	A company's internal control over financial reporting is a process designed to provide reasonable assurance regarding the reliability of financial reporting and the preparation of financial statements for external purposes in accordance with generally accepted accounting principles. A company's internal control over financial reporting includes those policies and procedures that
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;COLOR:#000000;">
	(a)
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	pertain to the maintenance of records that, in reasonable detail, accurately and fairly reflect the transactions and dispositions of the assets of the company;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;COLOR:#000000;">
	(b)
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	provide reasonable assurance that transactions are recorded as necessary to permit preparation of financial statements in accordance with generally accepted accounting principles, and that receipts and expenditures of the company are being made only in accordance with authorizations of management and directors of the company; and
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;COLOR:#000000;">
	(c)
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	provide reasonable assurance regarding prevention or timely detection of unauthorized acquisition, use, or disposition of the company's assets that could have a material effect on the financial statements.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;LINE-HEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;LINE-HEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	Because of its inherent limitations, internal control over financial reporting may not prevent or detect misstatements. Also, projections of any evaluation of effectiveness to future periods are subject to the risk that controls may become inadequate because of changes in conditions, or that the degree of compliance with the policies or procedures may deteriorate.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;LINE-HEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;LINE-HEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	In our opinion, The Hackett Group, Inc. maintained, in all material respects, effective internal control over financial reporting as of January 1, 2016, based on criteria established in
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;COLOR:#000000;">
	Internal Control &#x2014; Integrated Framework
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	issued by the Committee of Sponsoring Organizations of the Treadway Commission in 2013.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;LINE-HEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;LINE-HEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	We have also audited, in accordance with the standards of the Public Company Accounting Oversight Board (United States), the consolidated balance sheet of The Hackett Group, Inc. as of January 1, 2016, and the related consolidated statements of operations, comprehensive income, shareholders' equity, and cash flows of The Hackett Group, Inc. for the year ended January 1, 2016 and our report dated
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	March 16, 2016
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	expressed an unqualified opinion.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;LINE-HEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">

</P>

</P>

<EFX_COMPENSATION>
<A NAME="FIS_COMPENSATION"></A>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:13.5PT 0PT 0PT 55.05PT;TEXT-INDENT: -55.1PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<A NAME="HCKT-20160101X10K_HTM_ITEM11">
</A>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	ITEM&nbsp; 11
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;TEXT-INDENT:0PT;MARGIN-LEFT:0PT;PADDING:0PT 31PT 0PT 0PT;">
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	EXECUTIVE COMPENSATION

</FONT>

<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 7.2PT 0PT 0PT;LINE-HEIGHT:NORMAL;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;FONT-FAMILY:CENTURY SCHOOLBOOK;FONT-SIZE: 12PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 7.2PT 0PT 0PT;LINE-HEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-FAMILY:CENTURY SCHOOLBOOK;FONT-SIZE: 12PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:6PT 7.2PT 6PT 0PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;FONT-FAMILY:CENTURY SCHOOLBOOK;FONT-SIZE: 12PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CENTURY;">
	This Performance Based Stock Appreciation Right Agreement (the &#x201C;SAR Agreement&#x201D;) is made as of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CENTURY;">
	March 11
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CENTURY;">
	, 2013
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CENTURY;">
	(the &#x201C;Effective Date&#x201D;)
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CENTURY;">
	, &nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CENTURY;">
	by and between The Hackett Group, Inc., a Florida corporation (the &#x201C;Company&#x201D;), and
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CENTURY;">
	David N. Dungan
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CENTURY;">
	, an individual who is employed by, or providing
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CENTURY;">
	S
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CENTURY;">
	ervices to, the Company or one of its Affiliates or Service Providers (the "Grantee").
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CENTURY;">
	&nbsp;To the extent any capitalized words used in this Stock Appreciation Right Agreement are not defined, they shall have the definitions
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CENTURY;">
	assigned to
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CENTURY;">
	them in the Plan.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:6PT 7.2PT 6PT 0PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;FONT-FAMILY:CENTURY SCHOOLBOOK;FONT-SIZE: 12PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CENTURY;">
	WHEREAS, the Board of Directors and stockholders of the Company have duly adopted and approved The Hackett Group, Inc. 1998 Stock Option and Incentive Plan
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CENTURY;">
	, as amended
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CENTURY;">
	(the "Plan"), which Plan authorizes the Company to grant to eligible individuals Options, Restricted Stock, Restricted Stock Units, Stock Appreciation Rights and Other Awards;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:CENTURY SCHOOLBOOK;FONT-SIZE: 12PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CENTURY;">
	WHEREAS, in accordance with the Plan,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CENTURY;">
	on February 8, 2012,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CENTURY;">
	the Company granted the Grantee an Option to purchase an aggregate of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CENTURY;">
	1,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CENTURY;">
	004,063
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CENTURY;">
	shares of common stock, par value $0.0
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CENTURY;">
	0
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CENTURY;">
	1 per share of Stock of the Company at an exercise price of $
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CENTURY;">
	4.00
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CENTURY;">
	per share;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CENTURY;">
	and
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:CENTURY SCHOOLBOOK;FONT-SIZE: 12PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CENTURY;">
	WHEREAS, the Grantee voluntarily has agreed to replace the Option with a Stock Appreciation Right (as defined in Section 1, below) with the same material terms
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CENTURY;">
	as the Option
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CENTURY;">
	, that
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CENTURY;">
	will
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CENTURY;">
	be settled in cash
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CENTURY;">
	or
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CENTURY;">
	shares of the Company&#x2019;s common
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CENTURY;">
	stock at the Company&#x2019;s
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CENTURY;">
	sole discretion
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CENTURY;">
	.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CENTURY;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:6PT 7.2PT 6PT 0PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;FONT-FAMILY:CENTURY SCHOOLBOOK;FONT-SIZE: 12PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CENTURY;">
	NOW, THEREFORE, in consideration of the mutual promises and covenants contained herein, the parties hereto do hereby agree as follows:
</FONT>
</P>

	Conversion of Stock Option to Stock Appreciation Rights
</FONT>
</P>
</TD>

<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 7.2PT 0PT 0PT;FONT-FAMILY:CENTURY SCHOOLBOOK;FONT-SIZE: 12PT">
<FONT STYLE="TEXT-INDENT:0PT;MARGIN-LEFT:0PT; PADDING-RIGHT:106PT;">
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="TEXT-INDENT:0PT;MARGIN-LEFT:0PT; PADDING-RIGHT:4PT;TEXT-ALIGN:LEFT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CENTURY;COLOR:#000000;">
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CENTURY;COLOR:#000000;">
	The Grantee hereby
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CENTURY;COLOR:#000000;">
	voluntarily
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CENTURY;COLOR:#000000;">
	agrees to convert his Option into
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CENTURY;COLOR:#000000;">
	a stock appreciation right, to be settled in cash
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CENTURY;COLOR:#000000;">
	or shares of the Company&#x2019;s common stock
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CENTURY;COLOR:#000000;">
	at
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CENTURY;COLOR:#000000;">
	the Company&#x2019;s sole discretion
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CENTURY;COLOR:#000000;">
	in an amount
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CENTURY;COLOR:#000000;">
	corresponding to the appreciation over time of the value
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CENTURY;COLOR:#000000;">
	of 1,004,063
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CENTURY;COLOR:#000000;">
	shares of Company Stock (a &#x201C;Stock Appreciation Rights&#x201D; or &#x201C;SARs&#x201D;).&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CENTURY;COLOR:#000000;">
	Except and unless set forth in this SAR Agreement, s
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CENTURY;COLOR:#000000;">
	uch SARs will be governed by the Plan and the terms and conditions
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CENTURY;COLOR:#000000;">
	set forth
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CENTURY;COLOR:#000000;">
	in the
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CENTURY;COLOR:#000000;">
	Stock
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CENTURY;COLOR:#000000;">
	Option Agreement (attached
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CENTURY;COLOR:#000000;">
	hereto
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CENTURY;COLOR:#000000;">
	as Appendix A)
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CENTURY;COLOR:#000000;">
	, including, without limitation the terms relating to
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CENTURY;COLOR:#000000;">
	the Exercise Price,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CENTURY;COLOR:#000000;">
	vesting, term and termination
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CENTURY;COLOR:#000000;">
	.&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CENTURY;COLOR:#000000;">
	Except as provided in Section
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CENTURY;COLOR:#000000;">
	2 &nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CENTURY;COLOR:#000000;">
	below, the Grantee shall have none of the rights of a stockholder.

<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	2
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	. &nbsp;
</FONT>
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="TEXT-INDENT:0PT;MARGIN-LEFT:0PT; PADDING-RIGHT:4PT;TEXT-ALIGN:LEFT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	DIVIDEND
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	EQUIVALENT RIGHTS
</FONT>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:9PT 0PT 0PT;TEXT-INDENT:48.95PT;FONT-FAMILY:CENTURY SCHOOLBOOK;FONT-SIZE: 12PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CENTURY;">
	The Grantee
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CENTURY;">
	shall be awarded
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CENTURY;">
	dividend equivalent rights (&#x201C;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CENTURY;">
	DERs
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CENTURY;">
	&#x201D;)
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CENTURY;">
	with respect
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CENTURY;">
	to the shares of Stock underlying the SAR
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CENTURY;">
	s
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CENTURY;">
	that have vested
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CENTURY;">
	as of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CENTURY;">
	the date the dividend is
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CENTURY;">
	declared
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CENTURY;">
	. &nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CENTURY;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CENTURY;">
	Each DER will be
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CENTURY;">
	awarded
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CENTURY;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CENTURY;">
	to the Grantee
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CENTURY;">
	as a specific dollar amount equal to the dollar amount of the dividend paid on an actual
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CENTURY;">
	s
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CENTURY;">
	hare
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CENTURY;">
	of Stock
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CENTURY;">
	on
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CENTURY;">
	the date the dividend is
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CENTURY;">
	declared
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CENTURY;">
	multiplied by the
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CENTURY;">
	number of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CENTURY;">
	shares underlying the
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CENTURY;">
	Grantee&#x2019;s
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CENTURY;">
	SAR
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CENTURY;">
	. &nbsp;

</P>

<TD VALIGN="TOP" STYLE="WIDTH:26.95PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-LEFT:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-RIGHT:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;HEIGHT:20.65PT;PADDING:0PT;">
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 8PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;FONT-SIZE:8PT;">
	a)
</FONT>
</P>
</TD>
<TD VALIGN="TOP" STYLE="WIDTH:469.80PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-LEFT:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-RIGHT:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;HEIGHT:20.65PT;PADDING:0PT;">
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 8PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;FONT-SIZE:8PT;">
	All significant deficiencies and material weaknesses in the design or operation of internal control over financial reporting which are reasonably likely to adversely affect the registrant&#x2019;s ability to record, process, summarize and report financial information; and
</FONT>
</P>
</TD>
</TR>
</TABLE>
</DIV>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 4PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
